41 // __cpp_exceptions is referred from
42 // https://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/libstdc++/manual/using_exceptions.html
43 // gcc < 5 does not define __cpp_exceptions but __EXCEPTIONS,
44 // Microsoft C++ Compiler does not provide an option to disable exceptions
45 #ifndef DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS
46 #if __cpp_exceptions || __EXCEPTIONS \
47  || (defined(_MSC_VER) && !defined(__clang__))
48 #define DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS 1
49 #else
50 #define DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS 0
51 #endif
52 #endif
53 
54 #if defined(__GNUC__) || defined(__clang__)
55 #define DNNL_TRAP() __builtin_trap()
56 #elif defined(__INTEL_COMPILER) || defined(_MSC_VER)
57 #define DNNL_TRAP() __debugbreak()
58 #else
59 #error "unknown compiler"
60 #endif
61 
62 #if DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS
63 #define DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, msg) throw error(status, msg)
64 #else
65 #include <cstdio>
66 #define DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, msg) \
67  do { \
68  fputs(msg, stderr); \
69  DNNL_TRAP(); \
70  } while (0)
71 #endif

87 struct error : public std::exception {
88  dnnl_status_t status;
89  const char *message;
90 
95  error(dnnl_status_t status, const char *message)
96  : status(status), message(message) {}
97 
99  const char *what() const noexcept override { return message; }
100 
106  static void wrap_c_api(dnnl_status_t status, const char *message) {
107  if (status != dnnl_success) DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, message);
108  }
109 };
110 
112 template <typename T>
113 struct handle_traits {};
114 
128 template <typename T, typename traits = handle_traits<T>>
129 struct handle {
130 private:
131  static dnnl_status_t dummy_destructor(T) { return dnnl_success; }
132  std::shared_ptr<typename std::remove_pointer<T>::type> data_ {0};
133 
134 protected:
135  bool operator==(const T other) const { return other == data_.get(); }
136  bool operator!=(const T other) const { return !(*this == other); }
137 
138 public:
146  handle() = default;
147 
149  handle(const handle<T, traits> &) = default;
151  handle<T, traits> &operator=(const handle<T, traits> &) = default;
153  handle(handle<T, traits> &&) = default;
155  handle<T, traits> &operator=(handle<T, traits> &&) = default;
156 
162  explicit handle(T t, bool weak = false) { reset(t, weak); }
163 
169  void reset(T t, bool weak = false) {
170  data_.reset(t, weak ? &dummy_destructor : traits::destructor);
171  }
172 
178  T get(bool allow_empty = false) const {
179  T result = data_.get();
180  if (allow_empty == false && result == nullptr)
181  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(
182  dnnl_invalid_arguments, "object is not initialized");
183  return result;
184  }
185 
190  explicit operator T() const { return get(true); }
191 
195  explicit operator bool() const { return get(true) != nullptr; }
196 
203  bool operator==(const handle<T, traits> &other) const {
204  return other.data_.get() == data_.get();
205  }
206 
213  bool operator!=(const handle &other) const { return !(*this == other); }
214 };

360 dnnl::primitive::kind primitive::get_kind() const {
361  const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd = get_primitive_desc();
362  // TODO (Roma): the code below is only needed because get_primitive_desc
363  // returns a C type.
364  dnnl_primitive_kind_t kind;

366  pd, dnnl_query_primitive_kind, 0, (void *)&kind),
367  "could not get a primitive kind from a primitive descriptor");
368  return static_cast<dnnl::primitive::kind>(kind);
369 }

619 #define DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(enum_name) \
620  inline enum_name operator|(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
621  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
622  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
623  } \
624 \
625  inline enum_name operator&(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
626  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
627  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
628  } \
629 \
630  inline enum_name operator^(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
631  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
632  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
633  } \
634 \
635  inline enum_name &operator|=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
636  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
637  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
638  return lhs; \
639  } \
640 \
641  inline enum_name &operator&=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
642  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
643  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
644  return lhs; \
645  } \
646 \
647  inline enum_name &operator^=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
648  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
649  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
650  return lhs; \
651  } \
652 \
653  inline enum_name operator~(enum_name rhs) { \
654  return static_cast<enum_name>(~static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
655  }
656 
657 DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(normalization_flags)
658 DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(rnn_flags)

970  void get_output_scales(int &mask, std::vector<float> &scales) const {
971  dnnl_dim_t count;
972  int c_mask;
973  const float *c_scales;
974  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_attr_get_output_scales(
975  get(), &count, &c_mask, &c_scales),
976  "could not get primitive output scales attribute");
977  scales.resize(count);
978 
979  mask = c_mask;
980  for (dnnl_dim_t c = 0; c < count; ++c)
981  scales[c] = c_scales[c];
982  }

1191  void set_rnn_data_qparams(float scale, float shift) {

1194  "could not get primitive RNN data quantization parameters "
1195  "attributes");
1196  }

1248 template <>
1249 struct handle_traits<dnnl_engine_t> {
1250  static constexpr auto destructor = &dnnl_engine_destroy;
1251 };
1253 
1255 struct engine : public handle<dnnl_engine_t> {
1256  friend struct primitive;
1257  friend struct reorder;
1258 
1260  enum class kind {
1262  any = dnnl_any_engine,
1264  cpu = dnnl_cpu,
1266  gpu = dnnl_gpu,
1267  };
1268 
1269  using handle::handle;
1270 
1273  engine() = default;
1274 
1279  static size_t get_count(kind kind) {
1280  return dnnl_engine_get_count(convert_to_c(kind));
1281  }
1282 
1288  engine(kind kind, size_t index) {
1289  dnnl_engine_t engine;
1290  error::wrap_c_api(
1291  dnnl_engine_create(&engine, convert_to_c(kind), index),
1292  "could not create an engine");
1293  reset(engine);
1294  }
1295 
1296 #if DNNL_GPU_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_OCL
1297  engine(kind kind, cl_device_id device, cl_context context) {
1304  dnnl_engine_t engine;
1305  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_create_ocl(
1306  &engine, convert_to_c(kind), device, context),
1307  "could not create an engine");
1308  reset(engine);
1309  }
1310 #endif
1311 
1316  engine(const handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_t> &pd) {
1317  dnnl_engine_t c_engine;
1318  error::wrap_c_api(
1319  dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd.get(),
1320  dnnl::convert_to_c(dnnl::query::engine), 0, &c_engine),
1321  "could not get an engine from a primitive_desc");
1322  reset(c_engine, true);
1323  }
1324 
1327  kind get_kind() const {
1328  dnnl_engine_kind_t kind;
1329  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_get_kind(get(), &kind),
1330  "could not get kind of an engine");
1331  return static_cast<engine::kind>(kind);
1332  }
1333 
1334 #if DNNL_GPU_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_OCL
1335  cl_context get_ocl_context() const {
1338  cl_context context = nullptr;
1339  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_get_ocl_context(get(), &context),
1340  "could not get an OpenCL context fron an engine");
1341  return context;
1342  }
1343 
1346  cl_device_id get_ocl_device() const {
1347  cl_device_id device = nullptr;
1348  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_get_ocl_device(get(), &device),
1349  "could not get an OpenCL device fron an engine");
1350  return device;
1351  }
1352 #endif
1353 
1359  template <class primitive_desc>
1360  static engine query(const primitive_desc &pd) {
1361  return query(pd, dnnl::query::engine);
1362  }
1363 
1364 private:
1365  static dnnl_engine_kind_t convert_to_c(kind kind) {
1366  return static_cast<dnnl_engine_kind_t>(kind);
1367  }
1368 
1369  template <class primitive_desc>
1370  static engine query(const primitive_desc &pd, dnnl::query what) {
1371  dnnl_engine_t c_engine;
1372  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd.get(),
1373  dnnl::convert_to_c(what), 0, &c_engine),
1374  "could not get an engine from a primitive_desc");
1375  return engine(c_engine, true);
1376  }
1377 };

1397 struct stream : public handle<dnnl_stream_t> {
1398  using handle::handle;
1399 
1401  enum class flags : unsigned {
1404  default_order = dnnl_stream_default_order,
1406  in_order = dnnl_stream_default_order,
1408  out_of_order = dnnl_stream_out_of_order,
1410  default_flags = dnnl_stream_default_flags,
1411  };
1412 
1415  stream() = default;
1416 
1422  stream(const engine &engine, flags flags = flags::default_flags) {
1423  dnnl_stream_t stream;
1424  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_create(&stream, engine.get(),
1425  static_cast<dnnl_stream_flags_t>(flags)),
1426  "could not create a stream");
1427  reset(stream);
1428  }
1429 
1430 #if DNNL_GPU_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_OCL
1431  stream(const engine &engine, cl_command_queue queue) {
1436  dnnl_stream_t stream;
1437  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_create_ocl(&stream, engine.get(), queue),
1438  "could not create a stream");
1439  reset(stream);
1440  }
1441 
1444  cl_command_queue get_ocl_command_queue() const {
1445  cl_command_queue queue = nullptr;
1446  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_get_ocl_command_queue(get(), &queue),
1447  "could not get an OpenCL command queue from a stream");
1448  return queue;
1449  }
1450 #endif
1451 
1454  stream &wait() {
1455  error::wrap_c_api(
1456  dnnl_stream_wait(get()), "could not wait on a stream");
1457  return *this;
1458  }
1459 };

2058  struct desc {

2065  desc() : data() {}
2066 
2078  desc(const memory::dims &dims, data_type data_type,
2079  format_tag format_tag) {
2080  validate_dims(dims);
2081  error::wrap_c_api(
2082  dnnl_memory_desc_init_by_tag(&data, (int)dims.size(),
2083  dims.size() == 0 ? nullptr : &dims[0],
2084  convert_to_c(data_type), convert_to_c(format_tag)),
2085  "could not construct a memory descriptor using a format "
2086  "tag");
2087  }
2088 
2100  desc(const memory::dims &dims, data_type data_type,
2101  const memory::dims &strides) {
2102  validate_dims(dims);
2103  error::wrap_c_api(
2104  dnnl_memory_desc_init_by_strides(&data, (int)dims.size(),
2105  dims.size() == 0 ? nullptr : &dims[0],
2106  convert_to_c(data_type),
2107  strides.size() == 0 ? nullptr : &strides[0]),
2108  "could not construct a memory descriptor using strides");
2109  }
2110 
2114  desc(const dnnl_memory_desc_t &data) : data(data) {}
2115 
2118  //
2123  desc submemory_desc(
2124  const memory::dims &dims, const memory::dims &offsets) const {
2125  dnnl_memory_desc_t sub_md;
2126  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_memory_desc_init_submemory(
2127  &sub_md, &data, &dims[0], &offsets[0]),
2128  "could not construct a sub-memory");
2129  return desc(sub_md);
2130  }
2131 
2133  //
2137  desc reshape(const memory::dims &dims) const {
2138  dnnl_memory_desc_t out_md;
2139  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_memory_desc_reshape(&out_md, &data,
2140  (int)dims.size(), &dims[0]),
2141  "could not reshape a memory descriptor");
2142  return desc(out_md);
2143  }
2144

2150  return memory::dims(data.dims, data.dims + data.ndims);
2151  }
2152

2156  return static_cast<memory::data_type>(data.data_type);
2157  }
2158 
2163  size_t get_size() const { return dnnl_memory_desc_get_size(&data); }
2164 
2168  bool is_zero() const { return data.ndims == 0; }
2169 
2174  bool operator==(const desc &other) const {
2175  return dnnl_memory_desc_equal(&data, &other.data) != 0;
2176  }
2177 
2182  bool operator!=(const desc &other) const { return !operator==(other); }
2183  };

2355 struct primitive_desc_base : public handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_t> {

2368  get(), dnnl_query_impl_info_str, 0, &res),
2369  "could not retrieve implementation info string from a "
2370  "primitive descriptor");

2375  memory::dim query_s64(query what) const {
2376  memory::dim res;
2377  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
2378  get(), dnnl::convert_to_c(what), 0, &res);
2379  return status == dnnl_success ? res : 0;
2380  }
2381 
2396  memory::desc query_md(query what, int idx = 0) const {
2397  std::vector<query> valid_q {query::src_md, query::diff_src_md,
2398  query::weights_md, query::diff_weights_md, query::dst_md,
2399  query::diff_dst_md, query::workspace_md, query::scratchpad_md,
2400  query::exec_arg_md};
2401  if (!std::any_of(valid_q.cbegin(), valid_q.cend(),
2402  [=](query q) { return what == q; }))
2403  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
2404  "memory descriptor query is invalid");
2405 
2406  const dnnl_memory_desc_t *cdesc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query_md(
2407  get(), dnnl::convert_to_c(what), idx);
2408  return cdesc ? memory::desc(*cdesc) : memory::desc();
2409  }
2410 
2416  memory::desc src_desc(int idx) const {
2417  return query_md(query::src_md, idx);
2418  }
2419 
2425  memory::desc dst_desc(int idx) const {
2426  return query_md(query::dst_md, idx);
2427  }
2428 
2434  memory::desc weights_desc(int idx) const {
2435  return query_md(query::weights_md, idx);
2436  }
2437 
2443  memory::desc diff_src_desc(int idx) const {
2444  return query_md(query::diff_src_md, idx);
2445  }
2446 
2452  memory::desc diff_dst_desc(int idx) const {
2453  return query_md(query::diff_dst_md, idx);
2454  }
2455 
2461  memory::desc diff_weights_desc(int idx) const {
2462  return query_md(query::diff_weights_md, idx);
2463  }
2464

2466  // purposes.
2467

2473

2535  primitive_attr get_primitive_attr() const {

2537  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_get_attr(get(), &const_c_attr),
2538  "could not get attributes from a primitive descriptor");
2539  dnnl_primitive_attr_t c_attr;
2540  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_attr_clone(&c_attr, const_c_attr),
2541  "could not clone primitive attributes");

2547  dnnl::primitive::kind get_kind() const {
2548  dnnl_primitive_kind_t kind;
2549  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(get(),
2550  dnnl_query_primitive_kind, 0, (void *)&kind),
2551  "could not get primitive kind from a primitive descriptor");
2552  return static_cast<dnnl::primitive::kind>(kind);
2553  }
2554 
2555 protected:
2559  void reset_with_clone(const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd) {
2560  dnnl_primitive_desc_t new_pd;
2561  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_clone(&new_pd, pd),
2562  "could not clone a primitive descriptor");
2563  reset(new_pd);
2564  }
2565 
2579  primitive_desc_base(
2580  dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd, dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind)
2581  : primitive_desc_base(pd, prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind::undef) {}
2582 
2594  primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
2595  dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind)
2596  : primitive_desc_base(pd, prim_kind, prop_kind, prop_kind) {}
2597 
2611  primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
2612  dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind1,
2613  dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind2) {
2614  // It is OK to pass an empty primitive descriptor
2615  if (pd == nullptr) return;
2616 
2617  dnnl_status_t rc;
2618 
2619  dnnl_primitive_kind_t c_prim_kind = convert_to_c(prim_kind);
2620  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind1 = convert_to_c(prop_kind1);
2621  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind2 = convert_to_c(prop_kind2);
2622 
2623  // Check that primitive kind matches
2624  dnnl_primitive_kind_t pd_kind;
2625  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
2626  pd, dnnl_query_primitive_kind, 0, (void *)&pd_kind);
2627  error::wrap_c_api(
2628  rc, "could not get primitive kind from a primitive descriptor");
2629  if (pd_kind != c_prim_kind)
2630  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
2631  "primitive descriptor operation kind mismatch");
2632 
2633  // Check that propagation kind matches
2634  dnnl_prop_kind_t pd_prop_kind;
2635  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
2636  pd, dnnl_query_prop_kind, 0, (void *)&pd_prop_kind);
2637 
2638  // Something went wrong
2639  if (rc != dnnl_success && rc != dnnl_unimplemented)
2640  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
2641  "could not get propagation kind from the primitive "
2642  "descriptor");
2643 
2644  // Everything is fine
2645  if ((rc == dnnl_unimplemented && c_prop_kind1 == dnnl_prop_kind_undef)
2646  || (rc == dnnl_success
2647  && (pd_prop_kind == c_prop_kind1
2648  || pd_prop_kind == c_prop_kind2))) {
2649  reset_with_clone(pd);
2650  return;
2651  }
2652 
2653  // We could get the propagation kind but there is a mismatch
2654  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
2655  "primitive descriptor propagation kind mismatch");
2656  }
2657 
2658 protected:
2659  using base = primitive_desc_base;
2660 };
2661

2674 struct reorder : public primitive {

2681 
2697  primitive_desc(const engine &src_engine, const memory::desc &src_md,
2698  const engine &dst_engine, const memory::desc &dst_md,
2699  const primitive_attr &attr = primitive_attr()) {
2700  dnnl_primitive_desc_t result;
2701  error::wrap_c_api(
2702  dnnl_reorder_primitive_desc_create(&result, &src_md.data,
2703  src_engine.get(), &dst_md.data, dst_engine.get(),
2704  attr.get()),
2705  "could not create a primitive descriptor for a reorder "
2706  "primitive");
2707  reset(result);
2708  }
2709 
2717  primitive_desc(const memory &src, const memory &dst,
2718  const primitive_attr &attr = primitive_attr()) {
2719  dnnl_primitive_desc_t result;
2720  auto src_md = src.get_desc();
2721  auto dst_md = dst.get_desc();
2722  error::wrap_c_api(
2723  dnnl_reorder_primitive_desc_create(&result, &src_md.data,
2724  src.get_engine().get(), &dst_md.data,
2725  dst.get_engine().get(), attr.get()),
2726  "could not create a primitive descriptor for a reorder "
2727  "primitive");
2728  reset(result);
2729  }
2730

2736  : primitive_desc_base(pd, dnnl::primitive::kind::reorder) {}
2737 
2740  engine get_src_engine() const {
2741  return engine::query(*this, dnnl::query::reorder_src_engine);
2742  }
2743 
2746  engine get_dst_engine() const {
2747  return engine::query(*this, dnnl::query::reorder_dst_engine);
2748  }
2749 
2751  memory::desc src_desc() const { return base::src_desc(0); }
2752 
2754  memory::desc dst_desc() const { return base::dst_desc(0); }
2755  };

2758  reorder() = default;
2759 
2762  reorder(const primitive_desc &pd) : primitive(pd.get()) {}
2763 
2771  reorder(const memory &src, const memory &dst,
2772  const primitive_attr &attr = primitive_attr())
2773  : primitive(primitive_desc(src, dst, attr).get()) {}
2774 
2775  using primitive::execute;
2776 
2783  void execute(stream stream, memory &src, memory &dst) const {
2784  primitive::execute(stream, {{DNNL_ARG_FROM, src}, {DNNL_ARG_TO, dst}});
2785  }

2799 inline std::vector<dnnl_memory_desc_t> convert_to_c(
2800  const std::vector<memory::desc> &mems) {
2801  std::vector<dnnl_memory_desc_t> c_mems;
2802  c_mems.reserve(mems.size());
2803  for (const auto &s : mems)
2804  c_mems.push_back(s.data);
2805  return c_mems;
2806 }

2912 struct sum : public primitive {
2914  struct primitive_desc : public primitive_desc_base {
2915  using primitive_desc_base::primitive_desc_base;
2916 
2918  primitive_desc() = default;
2919 
2937  primitive_desc(const memory::desc &dst,
2938  const std::vector<float> &scales,
2939  const std::vector<memory::desc> &srcs, const engine &engine,
2940  const primitive_attr &attr = primitive_attr()) {
2941  error::wrap_c_api(scales.size() == srcs.size()
2942  ? dnnl_success
2943  : dnnl_invalid_arguments,
2944  "counts of scales and sources are not equal");
2945 
2946  auto c_api_srcs = convert_to_c(srcs);
2947 
2948  dnnl_primitive_desc_t result;
2949  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_sum_primitive_desc_create(&result, &dst.data,
2950  (int)c_api_srcs.size(), &scales[0],
2951  &c_api_srcs[0], attr.get(), engine.get()),
2952  "could not create a primitive descriptor for a sum "
2953  "primitive");
2954  reset(result);
2955  }
2956 
2967  primitive_desc(const std::vector<float> &scales,
2968  const std::vector<memory::desc> &srcs, const engine &engine,
2969  const primitive_attr &attr = primitive_attr()) {
2970  error::wrap_c_api(scales.size() == srcs.size()
2971  ? dnnl_success
2972  : dnnl_invalid_arguments,
2973  "counts of scales and sources are not equal");
2974 
2975  auto c_api_srcs = convert_to_c(srcs);
2976  dnnl_primitive_desc_t result;
2977  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_sum_primitive_desc_create(&result, nullptr,
2978  (int)c_api_srcs.size(), &scales[0],
2979  &c_api_srcs[0], attr.get(), engine.get()),
2980  "could not create a primitive descriptor for a sum "
2981  "primitive");
2982  reset(result);
2983  }
2984 
2989  primitive_desc(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd)
2990  : primitive_desc_base(pd, dnnl::primitive::kind::sum) {}
2991 
2993  memory::desc src_desc(int idx = 0) const { return base::src_desc(idx); }
2994 
2996  memory::desc dst_desc() const { return base::dst_desc(0); }
2997  };
2998 
3000  sum() = default;
3001 
3004  sum(const primitive_desc &pd) : primitive(pd.get()) {}
3005 };
3006 
3008 
3011 
3014 struct primitive_desc : public primitive_desc_base {
3015  using primitive_desc_base::primitive_desc_base;
3016 
3017  primitive_desc() = default;
3018 
3041  primitive_desc(const_dnnl_op_desc_t desc, const primitive_attr *attr,
3042  const engine &engine, const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t hint_fwd_pd,
3043  bool allow_empty = false)
3044  : allow_empty_(allow_empty) {
3045  dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_t iterator = nullptr;
3046  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_create(&iterator,
3047  desc, attr ? attr->get() : nullptr, engine.get(), hint_fwd_pd);
3048  if (!allow_empty)
3049  error::wrap_c_api(
3050  status, "could not create a primitive descriptor iterator");
3051  pd_iterator.reset(iterator);
3052  fetch_impl();
3053  }
3054 
3059  bool next_impl() {
3060  dnnl_status_t status
3061  = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_next(pd_iterator.get());
3062  if (status == dnnl_iterator_ends) return false;
3063  error::wrap_c_api(
3064  status, "could not advance a primitive descriptor iterator");
3065  fetch_impl();
3066  return true;
3067  }
3068 
3069 private:
3070  bool allow_empty_ = false;
3071  handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_t> pd_iterator;
3072  void fetch_impl() {
3073  dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_fetch(
3074  pd_iterator.get(allow_empty_));
3075  error::wrap_c_api(pd != nullptr || allow_empty_ ? dnnl_success
3076  : dnnl_runtime_error,
3077  "could not fetch a primitive descriptor from a primitive "
3078  "descriptor iterator");
3079  reset(pd);
3080  }
3081 };

6855  memory::desc dst_iter_desc() const { return base::dst_desc(1); }
6856 
6859  memory::desc dst_iter_c_desc() const { return base::dst_desc(2); }
6860 
6863  memory::desc diff_src_layer_desc() const { return base::diff_src_desc(0); }
6864 
6869  memory::desc diff_src_iter_desc() const { return base::diff_src_desc(1); }
6870 
6873  memory::desc diff_src_iter_c_desc() const { return base::diff_src_desc(2); }
6874 
6877  memory::desc diff_weights_layer_desc() const {
6878  return base::diff_weights_desc(0);
6879  }
6880 
6883  memory::desc diff_weights_iter_desc() const {
6884  return base::diff_weights_desc(1);
6885  }
6886 
6891  memory::desc diff_bias_desc() const { return base::diff_weights_desc(2); }
6892 
6895  memory::desc diff_dst_layer_desc() const { return base::diff_dst_desc(0); }
6896 
6901  memory::desc diff_dst_iter_desc() const { return base::diff_dst_desc(1); }
6902 
6905  memory::desc diff_dst_iter_c_desc() const { return base::diff_dst_desc(2); }
6906 
6907 protected:
6908  using rnn_base = rnn_primitive_desc_base;
6909 
6910  // (Deliberately not using doxygen comments)
6911  //
6912  // Constructs an RNN primitive descriptor base from a C API primitive
6913  // descriptor while checking that it actually describes the expected
6914  // primitive by comparing propagation and primitive kinds. Caller can
6915  // pass two options propagation kinds. This is typically used to check
6916  // that propagation kind is inference or training forward propagation.
6917  //
6918  // @param pd C API primitive descriptor.
6919  // @param prop_kind1 Expected propagation kind.
6920  // @param prop_kind2 Expected propagation kind.
6921  // @param cell_kind Expected cell kind.
6922  rnn_primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
6923  dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind1, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind2,
6924  dnnl::algorithm cell_kind) {
6925  dnnl_rnn_desc_t *rnn_d;
6926  dnnl_status_t rc;
6927  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd, dnnl_query_rnn_d, 0, &rnn_d);
6928  error::wrap_c_api(rc,
6929  "could not retrieve a descriptor from a primitive descriptor "
6930  "for an RNN primitive");
6931 
6932  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind1 = convert_to_c(prop_kind1);
6933  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind2 = convert_to_c(prop_kind2);
6934  dnnl_alg_kind_t c_cell_kind = convert_to_c(cell_kind);
6935 
6936  bool ok = rnn_d->primitive_kind == dnnl_rnn
6937  && (rnn_d->prop_kind == c_prop_kind1
6938  || rnn_d->prop_kind == c_prop_kind2)
6939  && rnn_d->cell_kind == c_cell_kind;
6940 
6941  if (!ok)
6942  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
6943  "mismatch between expected and provided descriptors for an "
6944  "RNN primitive");
6945 
6946  reset_with_clone(pd);
6947  }
6948 };

9450 inline primitive::primitive(const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t c_pd) {
9451  dnnl_primitive_t result;
9452  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_create(&result, c_pd),
9453  "could not create a primitive");
9454  reset(result);
9455 }
9456 
9457 inline primitive::primitive(const primitive_desc &pd) : primitive(pd.get()) {}
9458 
9459 inline void primitive::execute(
9460  stream &stream, const std::unordered_map<int, memory> &args) const {
9461  std::vector<dnnl_exec_arg_t> c_args;
9462  c_args.reserve(args.size());
9463  for (const auto &a : args)
9464  c_args.push_back({a.first, a.second.get(true)});
9465 
9466  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_execute(get(), stream.get(),
9467  (int)c_args.size(), c_args.data()),
9468  "could not execute a primitive");
9469 }
